topic.title: Device Identification Block

body.p: The Device Identification Configuration block defines revision and identification information for the Switchtec device. This includes device and firmware revision information, vendor and product identification, and PCIe device type. There is also an option to specify an external SEEPROM device used to override a subset of the identification information. The optional SEEPROM feature can be useful in the manufacturing environment to simplify management of the flash image.

entry.p: These fields should be valid if "Use Default Identification" is ZERO.
Manufacturer Information: Component Vendor ID (8 bytes)
Reserved for TWI SEEPROM 10-bit ADDR expansion
